### Field : find_tiles()
``` lua
local function search_function( tile )
	return tile:get_team() == Team.Blue
end

local tile_list = field:find_tiles( search_function )
```
> The above snippet finds all the **Tiles** that are currently owned by the **Blue Team**.

This function iterates through all of the <%= @link_tile %>s on the battlefield, and returns a list of them that matches a specific criteria *(provided by a function)*.

#### Function Call
`field:find_tiles( search_function )`

#### Return Value
<%= @link_tile %> **`vector`**

#### Parameters
**`function`** `search_function`<br>
	&emsp;_A function that filters the <%= @link_tile %>s you **want** to include._<br>
	
``` lua
local function search_function( tile )
  return tile:get_team() == Team.Red
end
```

<aside class="notice"><code>search_function</code> requires <b>one</b> <%= @link_tile %> parameter and to return a <b><code>boolean</code></b>.<br>
Any <%= @link_tile %> that causes the function to return <code>true</code> will be added to the list.</aside>
